Version extraction improvements for automation (v1.4.4)

Context:
- User requested clean semver extraction for automation/CI-CD pipelines
- Previous version display mixed version with text: 'v1.4.2 - OAuth + SSE Ready!'
- Needed machine-readable version for automated validation

Changes implemented:
1. Updated SERVER_VERSION from 1.4.2 to 1.4.4
2. Added HTML span element with id='semver' for CSS selector extraction
3. Added data-version attribute for dataset extraction
4. Created new /version endpoint returning clean JSON with semver breakdown
5. Created scripts/check-version.sh for version synchronization validation

Extraction methods now available:
- JavaScript: document.querySelector('#semver').textContent
- JavaScript: document.querySelector('[data-version]').dataset.version
- API: GET /version returns {version, semver, major, minor, patch}
- API: GET /health includes version field
- Bash: scripts/check-version.sh validates all versions match

This enables:
- Automated deployment verification
- CI/CD pipeline version checks
- Package version synchronization
- Semantic version comparison
- Production readiness validation

The version is now cleanly extractable as '1.4.4' without any surrounding text or prefixes, making it suitable for automated tooling and deployment scripts.
